What is the Ice Cream Market?
Ice cream is a sweetened frozen dessert traditionally made from dairy products like milk and cream, combined with a variety of flavorings and ingredients such as fruits, nuts, and chocolate. It is typically sweetened with sugar or alternative sweeteners and often contains stabilizers and emulsifiers to maintain its characteristic smooth texture and consistency. While fundamentally a comfort food, the market has dramatically evolved to encompass a wide array of categories, including premium, plant-based, and functional offerings, catering to diverse consumer palates and dietary needs.
